now lets us add a button on a page 
so we have to write html then we have to connect html and js file and css file

------so here is code of html ---------
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- <script src="second.js"></script>
    <button type="button"> Player 1: Abhinav</button> -->
    <script src="second.js"></script>
    
    
</body>
</html>
-------here is code of js file i have given file name as second.js -------
const button =document.querySelector("button");

button.addEventListener("click",updateName);

function updateName(){
    const name =prompt("Enter a new name");
    button.textContent='player 1: ${name}';
}
---------here is css file-------
button {
    font-family: "helvetica neue", helvetica, sans-serif;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    border: 2px solid rgb(200 200 0 / 60%);
    background-color: rgb(0 217 217 / 60%);
    color: rgb(100 0 0 / 100%);
    box-shadow: 1px 1px 2px rgb(0 0 200 / 40%);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

so you can run the code you will abe to get a button on a page.

